From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Override screen dimensions at the system level

Detection vector: Screen fingerprinting reads screen.width, screen.height,
screen.availWidth, screen.availHeight, and devicePixelRatio. In headless
mode, Chromium reports default values (800x600 or 1024x768) that differ
from any real display. Even in headed mode, the exact dimensions uniquely
identify the display.

This patch allows screen dimensions to be set via command line flags,
overriding the platform's actual display values.

Surface: system
Closes: screen fingerprinting, MQ_SCREEN, PHANTOM_SCREEN

--- a/ui/display/screen.cc
+++ b/ui/display/screen.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ display::Display Screen::GetPrimaryDisplay() const {
+  // AgenticBrowser: if --ab-screen=WxH is set, override the primary
+  // display's resolution and scale factor.
+  if (!ab_screen_size_.IsEmpty()) {
+    display.set_bounds(ab_screen_size_);
+    display.set_work_area(ab_screen_work_area_);
+    display.set_device_scale_factor(ab_screen_scale_);
+  }
